<div class="grey-wrapper">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12">
        <h2>SCOTLAND: The Big Picture</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4">
        <div class="link-card-cloudinary image-margin" style="background-image: url('<%= image_path('community/SBP_logo.jpg') %>'); height: 270px;">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-8">
        <p>SCOTLAND: The Big Picture is rewriting nature’s story, seeking to return abundance and diversity of life to Scotland’s land and seas, so that wildlife can flourish and people thrive.</p>
        <p>Be part of the conversation and make some noise. Share SCOTLAND: The Big Picture's rewilding stories, visit local rewilding initiatives, and gain a better understanding, or a new perspective.</p>
        <h5><strong>Seasgair are proud to:</strong></h5>
        <ul>
          <li>Sponsor local rewilding projects</li>
          <li>Make a donation each time a guest buys a Spa Pack</li>
          <li>Help raise awareness and share the story</li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Be inspired, be involved. What <strong>you</strong> can do:</h5>
        <ul>
          <li>Download and enjoy <%= link_to 'Pinelands', 'https://www.scotlandbigpicture.com/Store/ebooks/ebook-pinelands', target: :_blank, class: 'green-link' %>, a book packed full of stunning photography and powerful images of Scottish nature</li>
          <li>Watch the <%= link_to 'Scottish Rewilding Alliance animation', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZR2sPQHUt_4', target: :_blank, class: 'green-link' %>
          </li>
          <li>Put wild into your everyday life. Begin to make small changes - <%= link_to 'MeWilding', 'https://www.scotlandbigpicture.com/Store/ebooks/mewilding-ebook', target: :_blank, class: 'green-link' %> is rewilding for everyone!</li>
          <li>Donate via the <%= link_to 'Seasgair Community Giving Page', 'https://www.scotlandbigpicture.com/donate-SeasgairLodges', target: :_blank, class: 'green-link' %></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
      <h2>Disability Snowsports UK (DSUK)</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-8">
      <p>‘When I became disabled my whole world changed. I needed something that would make me feel alive again, something that would make me feel the blood pumping around my body and give me the thrill that I needed in my life. Thank you DSUK!’ Claire, Adaptive Skier</p>
      <p>DSUK believe that taking part in adaptive snowsport has the power to transform a person’s relationship with not just their disability, but with all aspects of their lives. DSUK believe that all people have the right to access the unique physical, mental, and social benefits of snowsport, regardless of disability, injury, or experience.</p>
      <p>Their fantastic team of instructors, volunteers and members shows that DSUK really does change lives of disabled communities and their families.</p>
      <h5><strong>Seasgair are proud to:</strong></h5>
      <ul>
        <li>Make a donation from each guest booking</li>
        <li>Cheer Judith on, as she raced the Strathspey Steam train</li>
        <li>Raise funds by climbing Ben Nevis and taking part in the Aviemore Santa Run with our families</li>
      </ul>
      <h5>Be inspired, be involved. What <strong>you</strong> can do:</h5>
      <ul>
        <li>Find out more about DSUK’s work and exciting fundraising opportunities. Contact the team at <a href="mailto:fundraising@disabilitysnowsport.org.uk" class="green-link">fundraising@disabilitysnowsport.org.uk</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-4">
      <div class="link-card-cloudinary" style="background-image: url('<%= image_path('community/DSUK_logo.jpg') %>'); height: 320px;">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="grey-wrapper">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-xs-12">
        <h2>Save the Planet Academy</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-4">
        <div class="link-card-cloudinary image-margin" style="background-image: url('<%= image_path('community/STPA_logo.png') %>'); height: 220px; box-shadow: none;">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-8">
        <p><%= link_to 'Save The Planet Academy', 'https://www.savetheplanet.academy', target: :_blank, class: 'green-link' %> is an eco enterprise with a vision of creating a children’s forest. The website was created by Crieff based 10 year old Brandon Delaney in response to a school entrepreneur assignment.</p>
        <p>The website challenges schools, organisations and individuals to either buy eco-friendly products from the site which fund tree planting, or to plant trees themselves - at home, at school or in the community. The trees planted are logged on site and you can watch the Children’s Forest grow.</p>
        <p>The school educational programme empowers children to be ‘hands on’ and take action by sowing, planting and visiting trees. It also provides a wider focus around environmental, community and climate issues.</p>
        <h5><strong>Seasgair are proud to:</strong></h5>
        <ul>
          <li>Make a donation from each guest booking to fund two projects - Children's Forest (UK) and the Eden Reforestation Project working in Kenya</li>
          <li>Encourage everyone to be proactive and plant trees</li>
        </ul>
        <h5>Be inspired, be involved. What <strong>you</strong> can do:</h5>
        <ul>
          <li>Work together for a brighter future, take a look at the website and Facebook Page</li>
          <li>Make a difference, plant a tree at home. Map it on the website and watch the Children’s Forest grow</li>
          <li>Sponsor a local tree champion to plant a tree in your name</li>
          <li>Become a tree champion - engage your school in the educational programme</li>
          <li>Support the Eden Reforestation Project working in Kenya, shop the eco-friendly products on site</li>
          <li>Start your own initiative via the Eco-Refill Station business in a box</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

